@startuml
' @id(CMP-VIEWER-THEME)
' @ref(USE-VIEWER-THEMED)
' @desc(CMP-VIEWER-THEME, "A new theming module inside the mdd-viewer crate that owns the bundled UI font assets and the per-frame OS-appearance-following Catppuccin theme. Pure chrome — it depends on egui through catppuccin_egui and on the OS through dark-light, but never touches the SVG render/font pipeline.")
' Objective-side component view for the Tier-1 theming change. It
' sits between MddViewer and egui::Context; CMP-VIEWER-RENDER-PIPELINE
' (the SVG side) is intentionally not in this diagram.
title mdd-viewer theming module — ownership (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev

component "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
component "theme.rs\nregister_fonts + apply_theme" as Theme
component "Bundled assets\nInter-Regular.ttf\nInter-Medium.ttf\nJetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf" as Assets
package "External crates" {
  component "catppuccin_egui\n0.x" as Catppuccin
  component "dark-light\n1.x" as DarkLight
}
component "egui::Context" as Ctx

Viewer --> Theme : construct\n+ each frame
Theme --> Assets : include_bytes!
Theme --> Ctx : set_fonts(FontDefinitions)
Theme --> DarkLight : detect() each frame
DarkLight --> Theme : Dark | Light | Default
Theme --> Catppuccin : set_theme(ctx, MOCHA | LATTE)
Catppuccin --> Ctx : style.visuals = ...
Theme --> Ctx : style_mut() spacing + rounding overrides
Ctx --> Dev : themed panels, toolbar, canvas chrome

note bottom of Theme
  Pure chrome boundary: theme.rs has no
  knowledge of ModelRegistry, CycleRegistry,
  CanvasView, or PanelLayout. Adding or
  removing it does not change any model or
  any rendered SVG; it only changes how
  egui paints widgets.
end note

note bottom of Assets
  TTFs ship inside the binary via
  include_bytes!. Licences (SIL OFL for
  Inter, OFL for JetBrains Mono) are
  carried alongside the assets and noted
  in the crate's NOTICE.
end note
@enduml
